DisplayedItem.title: # Lymph nodes designated as pelvic (parametrial, obturator, internal iliac (hypogastric), external iliac, common iliac, sacral, presacral) and para-aortic are considered regional lymph nodes. Any other involved nodes should be categorized as metastases (pM1) and reported in the distant metastasis section. Presence of isolated tumor cells no greater than 0.2 mm in regional lymph node(s) is considered N0 (i+).

DisplayedItem.title: Macrometastases (greater than 2 mm), Micrometastases (greater than 0.2 mm to 2 mm), Isolated Tumor Cells (ITC: less than or equal to 0.2 mm or single cells or clusters of cells less than or equal to 200 cells in a single lymph node cross section). If pelvic and / or para-aortic lymph nodes are submitted and positive for tumor cells, reporting the number of nodes with or without macrometastases and micrometastases is required. Reporting isolated tumor cells is required only in the absence of macrometastasis or micrometastasis.

Question.name: Q_937439
Question.title: FIGO Stage (2023 staging for cancer of the endometrium) (Note M)

ListItem.name: LI_937440
ListItem.title: I: Confined to the uterine corpus and ovary

ListItem.name: LI_937441
ListItem.title: IA: Disease limited to the endometrium OR non-aggressive histological type, i.e., low-grade endometrioid, with invasion of less than half of the myometrium with no or focal lymphovascular space involvement (LVSI) OR good prognosis disease

ListItem.name: LI_937442
ListItem.title: IA1: Non-aggressive histological type limited to an endometrial polyp OR confined to the endometrium

ListItem.name: LI_937443
ListItem.title: IA2: Non-aggressive histological types involving less than half of the myometrium with no or focal LVSI

ListItem.name: LI_937444
ListItem.title: IA3: Low-grade endometrioid carcinomas limited to the uterus and ovary

ListItem.name: LI_937445
ListItem.title: IAm (POLEmut): POLE mutated endometrial carcinoma, confined to the uterine corpus or with cervical extension, regardless of the degree of LVSI or histological type

ListItem.name: LI_937446
ListItem.title: IB: Non-aggressive histological types with invasion of half or more of the myometrium, and with no or focal LVSI

ListItem.name: LI_937447
ListItem.title: IC: Aggressive histological types limited to a polyp or confined to the endometrium

ListItem.name: LI_937448
ListItem.title: II: Invasion of cervical stroma without extrauterine extension OR with substantial LVSI OR aggressive histological types with myometrial invasion

ListItem.name: LI_937449
ListItem.title: IIA: Invasion of the cervical stroma of non-aggressive histological types

ListItem.name: LI_937450
ListItem.title: IIB: Substantial LVSI of non-aggressive histological types

ListItem.name: LI_937451
ListItem.title: IIC: Aggressive histological types with any myometrial involvement

ListItem.name: LI_937452
ListItem.title: IICm (p53abn): p53 abnormal endometrial carcinoma confined to the uterine corpus with any myometrial invasion, with or without cervical invasion, and regardless of the degree of LVSI or histological type

ListItem.name: LI_937453
ListItem.title: III: Local and / or regional spread of the tumor of any histological subtype

ListItem.name: LI_937454
ListItem.title: IIIA: Invasion of uterine serosa, adnexa, or both by direct extension or metastasis

ListItem.name: LI_937455
ListItem.title: IIIA1: Spread to ovary or fallopian tube (except when meeting stage IA3 criteria)

ListItem.name: LI_937456
ListItem.title: IIIA2: Involvement of uterine subserosa or spread through the uterine serosa

ListItem.name: LI_937457
ListItem.title: IIIB: Metastasis or direct spread to the vagina and / or to the parametria or pelvic peritoneum

ListItem.name: LI_937458
ListItem.title: IIIB1: Metastasis or direct spread to the vagina and / or the parametria

ListItem.name: LI_937459
ListItem.title: IIIB2: Metastasis to the pelvic peritoneum

ListItem.name: LI_937460
ListItem.title: IIIC: Metastasis to pelvic or para-aortic lymph nodes or both

ListItem.name: LI_937461
ListItem.title: IIIC1: Metastasis to the pelvic lymph nodes

ListItem.name: LI_937464
ListItem.title: IIIC2: Metastasis to para-aortic lymph nodes up to the renal vessels, with or without metastasis to the pelvic lymph nodes

ListItem.name: LI_937465
ListItem.title: IIIC2i: Micrometastasis (to para-aortic lymph nodes up to the renal vessels, with or without metastasis to the pelvic nodes)

ListItem.name: LI_937466
ListItem.title: IIIC2ii: Macrometastasis (to para-aortic lymph nodes up to the renal vessels, with or without metastasis to the pelvic nodes)

ListItem.name: LI_937467
ListItem.title: IV: Spread to the bladder mucosa and / or intestinal mucosa and / or distant metastasis

ListItem.name: LI_937468
ListItem.title: IVA: Invasion of the bladder mucosa and / or intestine / bowel mucosa

ListItem.name: LI_937469
ListItem.title: IVB: Abdominal peritoneal metastasis beyond the pelvis

ListItem.name: LI_937470
ListItem.title: IVC: Distant metastasis, including metastasis to any extra- or intra-abdominal lymph nodes above the renal vessels, lungs, liver, brain or bone
